1
00:00:04,794 --> 00:00:07,695
<i>THE FILM YOU ARE ABOUT
TO SEE WON TWO AWARDS</i>

2
00:00:07,797 --> 00:00:11,756
<i>AT THE 1956 VENICE FILM FESTIVAL:</i>

3
00:00:11,868 --> 00:00:17,773
<i>THE FIPRESCI PRIZE</i>

4
00:00:17,874 --> 00:00:23,779
<i>AND
THE BEST ACTRESS AWARD</i>

5
00:02:53,546 --> 00:02:55,269
<i>Morning came</i>

6
00:02:56,778 --> 00:02:58,600
<i>and he still hadn't returned.</i>

7
00:02:58,698 --> 00:03:00,935
<i>He'd been out all night.</i>

8
00:03:01,034 --> 00:03:03,139
<i>It was the first time.</i>

9
00:03:03,242 --> 00:03:06,591
<i>I was so proud to have
the handsomest guy around,</i>

10
00:03:07,594 --> 00:03:10,016
<i>me, the gimp.</i>

11
00:03:10,122 --> 00:03:11,529
Already up, Gervaise?

12
00:03:12,203 --> 00:03:14,407
Coming to the washhouse?

13
00:03:14,506 --> 00:03:16,416
I 'll save you a spot.

14
00:03:16,522 --> 00:03:18,529
Is Lantier still asleep?

15
00:03:18,635 --> 00:03:20,708
Yes, he's a bit tired.

16
00:03:30,635 --> 00:03:32,544
She's still there.

17
00:03:33,547 --> 00:03:35,435
She's not afraid to catch cold.

18
00:03:35,531 --> 00:03:37,898
She's patient.

19
00:03:42,955 --> 00:03:45,922
It's yours if you promise
to go home with it.

20
00:03:46,028 --> 00:03:47,850
- Dare me?
- Dare you.

21
00:03:56,076 --> 00:03:57,985
I don't give a damn.

22
00:04:06,155 --> 00:04:08,130
- Bye, Virginie.
- Have a nice trip!

23
00:04:14,475 --> 00:04:17,475
- I salute you, Mr. Boche.
- I return the salute.

24
00:04:17,580 --> 00:04:19,620
Like you turn out a coat.

25
00:04:19,724 --> 00:04:21,634
Like you turn the ladies' heads.

26
00:04:21,740 --> 00:04:23,944
Go ahead, she's gone.

27
00:04:24,044 --> 00:04:26,411
Don't you think
that's going too far?

28
00:04:26,508 --> 00:04:30,152
- Why? I like flowers.
- Go on, you rascal.

29
00:04:42,316 --> 00:04:44,487
There you are!

30
00:04:44,589 --> 00:04:47,306
- Where'd you spend the night?
- What night?

31
00:04:47,405 --> 00:04:50,187
You were with that whore next door!

32
00:04:50,285 --> 00:04:52,357
Take that back.

33
00:04:52,461 --> 00:04:54,665
You're picky!
Who were you with?

34
00:04:56,301 --> 00:05:00,578
- Why don't you shut up?
- You dare come in with a flower!

35
00:05:00,685 --> 00:05:03,052
Girls who sleep
with the whole neighborhood!

36
00:05:03,148 --> 00:05:05,036
Nice girls!

37
00:05:05,133 --> 00:05:06,060
Mommy!

38
00:05:06,157 --> 00:05:09,157
Shut them up or I'm leaving!

39
00:05:09,261 --> 00:05:12,163
If it weren't for them...
Poor babies!

40
00:05:12,269 --> 00:05:15,979
And your reputation!
- Fine.

41
00:05:16,077 --> 00:05:17,637
Listen, I'll tell you -

42
00:05:17,741 --> 00:05:19,813
I'll kill her!

43
00:05:19,917 --> 00:05:22,022
With my bare hands if I have to!

44
00:05:22,125 --> 00:05:23,784
And me too?

45
00:05:23,885 --> 00:05:26,536
Oh, no. Not you.

46
00:05:26,637 --> 00:05:28,044
Thanks.

47
00:05:28,781 --> 00:05:30,985
See? You're all worked up.

48
00:05:31,085 --> 00:05:33,157
Why? You didn't sleep?

49
00:05:33,261 --> 00:05:35,465
What did I do to you?

50
00:05:39,917 --> 00:05:40,865
Keep scrubbing!

51
00:05:42,830 --> 00:05:45,033
- It's filthy!
- I do my best.

52
00:05:47,086 --> 00:05:49,704
- Got money for lunch?
- How could l?

53
00:05:49,806 --> 00:05:51,529
By stealing?

54
00:05:53,005 --> 00:05:55,526
- Take this to the pawnshop.
- Again?

55
00:05:55,630 --> 00:05:56,645
Yes.

56
00:05:56,749 --> 00:05:58,604
I can't, I'm going to the washhouse.

57
00:05:58,702 --> 00:06:00,295
Why not say so?
I'll hock it, then.

58
00:06:01,037 --> 00:06:01,899
So...

59
00:06:03,310 --> 00:06:05,318
you'll bring back lunch?

60
00:06:06,030 --> 00:06:08,234
Not at the cheese shop,
we owe them for last week.

61
00:06:08,910 --> 00:06:10,820
Buy bread and some chops.

62
00:06:11,758 --> 00:06:12,935
Breaded chops?

63
00:06:13,038 --> 00:06:14,183
Yes.

64
00:06:15,022 --> 00:06:16,266
And a bottle of wine.

65
00:06:17,486 --> 00:06:20,137
- Red?
- Of course.

66
00:06:23,534 --> 00:06:25,901
See?

67
00:06:30,318 --> 00:06:32,685
It was all right, once again.

68
00:06:33,838 --> 00:06:37,635
All he had to do was smile at me

69
00:06:37,742 --> 00:06:39,979
and I'd end up saying, "Fine".

70
00:06:49,198 --> 00:06:51,565
They'll be clean, mutton chop.

71
00:06:59,439 --> 00:07:02,473
Hey, Gervaise!

72
00:07:03,151 --> 00:07:05,420
I saved you a spot!

73
00:07:05,519 --> 00:07:07,591
That's kind of you!

74
00:07:15,439 --> 00:07:18,854
You should've soaked those.

75
00:07:19,856 --> 00:07:23,085
I swear, those kids
with their sooty backsides!

76
00:07:23,184 --> 00:07:25,224
Get some soapy water.

77
00:07:25,327 --> 00:07:27,367
Don't worry,
just hot water will do fine.

78
00:07:27,472 --> 00:07:31,214
You know your stuff! You were
a laundress back home, weren't you?

79
00:07:31,312 --> 00:07:32,872
Yes, from the age of 10.

80
00:07:32,976 --> 00:07:34,863
Been in Paris long?

81
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:37,643
- Two months.
- Been married long?

82
00:07:38,640 --> 00:07:40,680
We're not married.

83
00:07:40,783 --> 00:07:43,304
No shame in that!

84
00:07:43,407 --> 00:07:44,968
It's for the best.

85
00:07:45,072 --> 00:07:47,439
He's not nice enough
to want to be his wife.

86
00:07:47,536 --> 00:07:49,391
What's his profession?

87
00:07:50,864 --> 00:07:53,711
- I'll get a bucket of hot water.
- Me too.

88
00:07:58,384 --> 00:08:00,107
Hello!

89
00:08:00,208 --> 00:08:01,866
Hello, Gervaise.

90
00:08:01,968 --> 00:08:04,107
It's his first birthday.

91
00:08:04,912 --> 00:08:06,636
He's teething.

92
00:08:13,552 --> 00:08:15,113
What's his profession?

93
00:08:16,112 --> 00:08:17,934
Hatter.

94
00:08:18,032 --> 00:08:19,407
Or it was.

95
00:08:19,504 --> 00:08:23,301
Since we've been in Paris,
he doesn't do much of anything.

96
00:08:23,409 --> 00:08:25,264
So he's not nice?

97
00:08:27,697 --> 00:08:29,453
Oh, not nice...

98
00:08:30,929 --> 00:08:33,296
It's been eight years.

99
00:08:33,393 --> 00:08:34,953
You can't ask much from a man.

100
00:08:35,057 --> 00:08:36,682
Skirt-chaser?

101
00:08:38,161 --> 00:08:41,161
- Why do you say that?
- No reason.

102
00:08:41,265 --> 00:08:42,988
Come on, why'd you say that?

103
00:08:43,089 --> 00:08:44,496
I thought you had.

104
00:08:44,593 --> 00:08:46,797
I was just repeating it.

105
00:08:46,897 --> 00:08:49,101
What about those
two girls at your house?

106
00:08:49,201 --> 00:08:51,023
Adèle and Virginie?

107
00:08:51,121 --> 00:08:53,488
Gervaise, what are you imagining?

108
00:08:54,161 --> 00:08:56,463
No need to imagine.
I know!

109
00:08:56,561 --> 00:08:59,082
- What do you know?
- It's either Adèle or Virginie!

110
00:08:59,185 --> 00:09:03,146
Nonsense! He might pinch them
on the stairs, but...

111
00:09:03,249 --> 00:09:06,249
On the stairs?
What's he doing on the stairs?

112
00:09:06,353 --> 00:09:10,477
Nothing!
I just said "on the stairs,"

113
00:09:10,577 --> 00:09:12,617
Iike I'd say "on the street."

114
00:09:12,722 --> 00:09:15,111
I said "on the stairs"
because it's my job to wash them.

115
00:09:17,201 --> 00:09:19,089
- Looking for someone?
- My mommy.

116
00:09:19,186 --> 00:09:21,968
- Who is she?
- My name's Etienne Lantier.

117
00:09:22,066 --> 00:09:23,921
- Charles!
- What?

118
00:09:24,017 --> 00:09:25,741
Two kids looking for their mother.

119
00:09:25,842 --> 00:09:27,664
I'll announce it.

120
00:09:28,466 --> 00:09:31,084
"Two kids are
looking for their mother!"

121
00:09:59,186 --> 00:10:01,553
- Why'd you bring me the key?
- Daddy left.

122
00:10:01,650 --> 00:10:04,170
Yes, to buy lunch.

123
00:10:04,275 --> 00:10:06,958
- He told you to get me?
- Daddy left.

124
00:10:07,058 --> 00:10:11,019
He put all his things in a trunk
and put it in the carriage

125
00:10:11,123 --> 00:10:12,530
and then he left.

126
00:10:12,626 --> 00:10:15,310
Was there a lady in the carriage?

127
00:10:15,411 --> 00:10:18,160
He packed all his things
and he left.

128
00:10:21,810 --> 00:10:26,088
Tell me who it was,
now that he's gone.

129
00:10:26,195 --> 00:10:28,432
Sure, now I will.
With her sister.

130
00:10:29,107 --> 00:10:31,474
Looks like she's here
just to see your face.

131
00:10:40,435 --> 00:10:42,923
What's your problem, ragamuffin?

132
00:10:44,403 --> 00:10:47,502
And a gimp, too!

133
00:10:48,372 --> 00:10:49,932
You don't scare me.

134
00:10:50,035 --> 00:10:51,661
I don't want to scare you.

135
00:10:51,764 --> 00:10:55,986
I want to hurt you!
- Tell me, what have I done to you?

136
00:10:56,083 --> 00:10:58,472
You know quite well!
My husband was seen -

137
00:10:58,580 --> 00:11:00,402
"My husband!"

138
00:11:00,500 --> 00:11:03,500
What husband?
She's not married!

139
00:11:08,180 --> 00:11:11,475
Attention! Lost husband!
Without a collar, no reward!

140
00:11:15,284 --> 00:11:16,844
Leave me alone.

141
00:11:16,948 --> 00:11:18,192
I've got work to do!

142
00:11:20,660 --> 00:11:23,181
It's your sister! I know it!

143
00:11:23,284 --> 00:11:25,488
Yes, it is.
Now you know! Happy?

144
00:11:26,612 --> 00:11:28,881
I didn't say a word
to that bitch.

145
00:11:28,980 --> 00:11:30,540
The nerve...

146
00:11:31,284 --> 00:11:33,007
Take that!

147
00:11:33,108 --> 00:11:35,148
Another dress ruined!

148
00:11:36,629 --> 00:11:38,189
Take that!

149
00:11:48,980 --> 00:11:50,541
And that!

150
00:11:53,109 --> 00:11:54,964
Not hot water!

151
00:12:12,405 --> 00:12:15,187
Charles!
Pull them apart!

152
00:12:15,285 --> 00:12:17,522
No way, last time
I almost lost an eye!

153
00:12:32,054 --> 00:12:33,876
We should stop them!

154
00:13:01,078 --> 00:13:02,484
Mommy!

155
00:13:22,646 --> 00:13:25,199
- No, l...
- Mommy!

156
00:13:40,983 --> 00:13:43,666
Now you'll see!

157
00:13:43,766 --> 00:13:45,708
This is for you!

158
00:13:45,815 --> 00:13:50,223
This is for your sister!
For your sister's sister!

159
00:13:50,327 --> 00:13:53,676
For Lantier!
For you!

160
00:13:53,783 --> 00:13:57,012
For your sister!

161
00:13:57,111 --> 00:13:59,893
Take that and that!

162
00:14:11,415 --> 00:14:14,197
Come on, Virginie.

163
00:14:16,631 --> 00:14:18,573
You haven't seen
the last of me, bitch!

164
00:14:29,847 --> 00:14:32,051
That'll be two cents.

165
00:14:40,184 --> 00:14:43,479
If that's the way it is,
I'll fight back.

166
00:14:44,184 --> 00:14:45,744
Alone

167
00:14:45,848 --> 00:14:47,921
with my two children.

168
00:14:50,168 --> 00:14:53,517
First of all, you say
I don 't have a husband?

169
00:14:54,552 --> 00:14:57,814
Yes, I do.
I got married.

170
00:15:00,792 --> 00:15:03,313
Yes, I got married.

171
00:15:06,488 --> 00:15:08,375
Mr. Coupeau married me.

172
00:15:09,688 --> 00:15:11,827
Even though, naturally,
I couldn 't be married in white like her.

173
00:15:16,088 --> 00:15:18,641
I borrowed a dress
from Coupeau 's sister.

174
00:15:18,745 --> 00:15:20,632
What misers they are!

175
00:15:21,369 --> 00:15:25,362
They work with gold,
making little chains.

176
00:15:25,465 --> 00:15:27,832
Working with gold
makes you nasty, it seems.

177
00:15:27,929 --> 00:15:29,838
- Hey, Lorilleux.
- What?

178
00:15:29,945 --> 00:15:32,465
Doesn't she look like Thérèse?

179
00:15:32,569 --> 00:15:35,187
You know, our neighbor
who died of pneumonia?

180
00:15:35,289 --> 00:15:37,296
There's a resemblance.

181
00:15:37,401 --> 00:15:40,216
And you have two children?

182
00:15:40,313 --> 00:15:43,859
I told my brother, why marry
a woman with two children?

183
00:15:43,961 --> 00:15:47,890
Don't be offended, I'm just
looking out for his best interests!

184
00:15:49,209 --> 00:15:51,544
What's more,
you don't look very healthy.

185
00:15:51,641 --> 00:15:53,681
- Doesn't look healthy, does she?
- Not really.

186
00:15:53,785 --> 00:15:57,047
That's enough! The wedding is tomorrow.
You don't have to come.

187
00:15:57,145 --> 00:15:59,000
Of course we're coming!
You're so touchy!

188
00:15:59,097 --> 00:16:00,658
Want the money
for our two dinners?

189
00:16:00,761 --> 00:16:03,249
Don't bother. Everyone will pay
their share afterwards. Good night.

190
00:16:03,353 --> 00:16:06,998
- Wait!
- Here comes the ceremony...

191
00:16:09,145 --> 00:16:13,106
We're careful because bits of gold might
stick to the soles and get carried off.

192
00:16:16,602 --> 00:16:19,701
Don't get mad! She'll show
her soles like everyone else!

193
00:16:25,690 --> 00:16:28,887
Of course he wasn't as classy as...

194
00:16:28,986 --> 00:16:31,768
But he was so nice!

195
00:16:31,866 --> 00:16:34,866
And roofing is a fine profession.

196
00:16:36,762 --> 00:16:39,031
You're so handsome!

197
00:16:39,930 --> 00:16:41,654
What about me?

198
00:16:43,130 --> 00:16:45,236
It looks great on you!

199
00:16:45,754 --> 00:16:46,998
But that's not all...

200
00:16:47,098 --> 00:16:49,651
That slob Mes Bottes stole
one of my patent-leather shoes!

201
00:16:51,386 --> 00:16:53,328
So we can't get married?

202
00:16:55,290 --> 00:16:57,178
I'll hop down the aisle!

203
00:17:10,651 --> 00:17:13,684
Perfect. Thank you, madam.

204
00:17:14,363 --> 00:17:16,730
Your turn, sir.

205
00:17:21,051 --> 00:17:22,873
Second thoughts?

206
00:17:23,771 --> 00:17:25,494
It's not that...

207
00:17:29,851 --> 00:17:32,120
- That counts, right?
- Naturally!

208
00:17:34,524 --> 00:17:36,891
BLlND

209
00:17:36,987 --> 00:17:39,890
Spare some change,
ladies and gents?

210
00:18:03,931 --> 00:18:07,095
- Blasted holy water!
- You're too late.

211
00:18:07,196 --> 00:18:09,716
That's quick work!

212
00:18:09,820 --> 00:18:12,024
It's like at the dentist's:
over before you can say "ouch!"

213
00:18:12,124 --> 00:18:14,098
Completely painless.

214
00:18:14,204 --> 00:18:16,408
The pain comes later.

215
00:18:19,612 --> 00:18:21,368
DEAF AND DUMB

216
00:18:29,212 --> 00:18:31,994
- What are you doing here?
- We came to get you.

217
00:18:32,092 --> 00:18:34,776
I said I'd come to dinner.
I don't have time now.

218
00:18:34,876 --> 00:18:38,521
- No protests!
- We need you to have fun!

219
00:18:39,420 --> 00:18:41,460
Have fun without me.

220
00:18:42,812 --> 00:18:44,951
Gervaise, ask him. He won't come.

221
00:18:46,588 --> 00:18:48,312
Careful with my dress!

222
00:18:52,092 --> 00:18:54,394
Ask him to come.

223
00:18:56,509 --> 00:18:59,226
Please come,
it'd make us so happy!

224
00:19:00,061 --> 00:19:03,509
In that case, I'll come.

225
00:19:04,668 --> 00:19:06,556
Come on.

226
00:19:09,149 --> 00:19:13,273
See those two kids?
My brother has a lot on his hands.

227
00:19:13,373 --> 00:19:15,991
- Stop it.
- But it's true.

228
00:19:16,093 --> 00:19:18,810
I've got hands too, I work.

229
00:19:18,910 --> 00:19:20,949
She's my best worker.

230
00:19:21,053 --> 00:19:23,126
She'll have her own shop
within 10 years.

231
00:19:23,229 --> 00:19:26,077
- If only it'd let up.
- It will never let up.

232
00:19:26,173 --> 00:19:28,694
We could take the avenue
up past the cemetery.

233
00:19:28,797 --> 00:19:31,765
You fetch me from the forge
to take me to a cemetery!

234
00:19:31,869 --> 00:19:33,364
That's a good one!

235
00:19:33,469 --> 00:19:35,127
I've got an idea.

236
00:19:35,230 --> 00:19:36,855
How about going to the museum?

237
00:19:36,957 --> 00:19:39,291
- What for?
- To have a look.

238
00:19:39,389 --> 00:19:41,331
Ever been to the Louvre?

239
00:19:41,438 --> 00:19:43,642
You should see it at least once.

240
00:19:45,630 --> 00:19:46,557
Fine.

241
00:19:50,397 --> 00:19:51,958
Etienne, Claude!

242
00:19:52,061 --> 00:19:53,370
What?

243
00:19:53,470 --> 00:19:56,634
- We're leaving.
- Sure, we're not going to rot here!

244
00:19:56,734 --> 00:19:59,484
It'll do everyone good.

245
00:20:34,622 --> 00:20:37,078
This one's really worth a look!

246
00:20:37,182 --> 00:20:40,150
It's all on the table, what a spread!

247
00:20:40,255 --> 00:20:43,386
I hope it'll whet your appetites for later.

248
00:20:44,383 --> 00:20:45,943
Look at that one puke!

249
00:20:48,383 --> 00:20:51,383
And that guy's watering the dandelions!

250
00:20:54,335 --> 00:20:55,448
Hey!

251
00:20:55,551 --> 00:20:57,755
Over here! Some real marvels!

252
00:21:08,991 --> 00:21:11,031
Now that's something!

253
00:21:11,871 --> 00:21:13,759
Look at the bride!

254
00:21:13,856 --> 00:21:15,994
She's blushing!

255
00:21:16,095 --> 00:21:19,095
My word, getting married
made her a virgin!

256
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:22,396
This isn't for kids! Come on,
there's some battles over here.

257
00:21:25,024 --> 00:21:27,544
Look over here, it's even better!

258
00:21:32,576 --> 00:21:34,398
With a swan!
Can you believe it?

259
00:21:34,496 --> 00:21:37,660
It was in ancient times, but still...

260
00:21:43,456 --> 00:21:45,049
Like it?

261
00:21:45,152 --> 00:21:48,381
Yes, I prefer that.
It's about something.

262
00:21:51,232 --> 00:21:53,174
I'm glad I wasn't there.

263
00:21:53,280 --> 00:21:54,840
I wish I had been.

264
00:21:57,408 --> 00:22:00,092
- Who is that lady?
- Liberty.

265
00:22:01,568 --> 00:22:04,535
No, he wasn't like everyone else.

266
00:22:07,521 --> 00:22:11,896
I wondered, "Why did he insist
that he come to the wedding?"

267
00:22:12,736 --> 00:22:16,598
He 's not cheerful,
he doesn 't make people laugh,

268
00:22:16,705 --> 00:22:19,574
his mind seems elsewhere.

269
00:22:20,737 --> 00:22:23,038
Then I thought,

270
00:22:23,136 --> 00:22:25,503
"lt must be because
Coupeau respects him."

271
00:23:10,658 --> 00:23:12,862
Watch out!

272
00:23:24,577 --> 00:23:26,301
My poor feet!

273
00:23:26,402 --> 00:23:28,573
Paris is so big!

274
00:23:28,674 --> 00:23:31,324
Please, you needn't bother.

275
00:23:32,002 --> 00:23:33,825
Must you be so formal?

276
00:23:36,098 --> 00:23:38,553
Don't bother, dear.

277
00:23:44,258 --> 00:23:45,916
Thanks.

278
00:23:49,538 --> 00:23:51,261
Walking in the streets wasn't bad,

279
00:23:51,362 --> 00:23:54,264
but the museum...

280
00:24:01,859 --> 00:24:03,419
That's enough.

281
00:24:04,706 --> 00:24:08,667
- That's enough, dear.
- Fine.

282
00:24:24,259 --> 00:24:27,041
Know how much we have
to set up housekeeping?

283
00:24:27,747 --> 00:24:29,154
Seven cents.

284
00:24:32,931 --> 00:24:35,135
Seven cents, seven cents

285
00:24:35,235 --> 00:24:37,624
To set up a home for two

286
00:24:39,843 --> 00:24:42,462
Seven cents, seven cents,

287
00:24:43,236 --> 00:24:44,643
Wife...

288
00:24:45,891 --> 00:24:47,931
What shall we do

289
00:24:58,052 --> 00:25:00,223
Time passed.

290
00:25:00,324 --> 00:25:01,982
The children grew.

291
00:25:02,084 --> 00:25:04,418
And then, I had Nana.

292
00:25:29,060 --> 00:25:31,744
We worked hard,

293
00:25:35,140 --> 00:25:37,660
he on the roofs,

294
00:25:37,765 --> 00:25:39,870
I at the laundry,

295
00:25:41,508 --> 00:25:44,508
because I was determined
to rent a shop

296
00:25:45,189 --> 00:25:49,313
and be my own boss.

297
00:25:58,245 --> 00:26:01,725
It's nice to bring me flowers.
Thanks.

298
00:26:09,733 --> 00:26:12,581
The shop is still for rent,
you know.

299
00:26:16,325 --> 00:26:18,048
But it's too expensive.

300
00:26:18,149 --> 00:26:21,182
It's not that.
Do you want to be the boss?

301
00:26:21,285 --> 00:26:22,267
Why not?

302
00:26:22,374 --> 00:26:25,538
You'll be good at it, I know you.

303
00:26:25,637 --> 00:26:27,198
Then what?

304
00:26:27,301 --> 00:26:29,668
No one likes the boss.

305
00:26:29,765 --> 00:26:32,132
I don't like
people not liking you.

306
00:26:32,230 --> 00:26:34,466
You're so silly!

307
00:26:40,518 --> 00:26:42,176
SHOP FOR RENT

308
00:26:42,278 --> 00:26:44,001
You don't understand.

309
00:26:44,102 --> 00:26:47,418
- But I have the money!
- He has to sign. That's the law.

310
00:26:48,806 --> 00:26:50,628
I'll go get him.

311
00:26:50,726 --> 00:26:52,898
- I'll be right back.
- We'll save it for you.

312
00:27:06,182 --> 00:27:08,484
There's Gervaise!

313
00:27:08,582 --> 00:27:10,851
Put the iron on the fire.

314
00:27:13,126 --> 00:27:16,388
Well? Did you rent the shop?

315
00:27:17,062 --> 00:27:18,688
No! You have to come!

316
00:27:18,790 --> 00:27:20,416
Why?

317
00:27:21,414 --> 00:27:22,342
To sign!

318
00:27:22,439 --> 00:27:23,999
I don't know how.

319
00:27:24,102 --> 00:27:28,325
- Make a cross. It's the law.
- Well, if it's the law...

320
00:27:28,422 --> 00:27:30,626
I'll be down in five minutes.

321
00:27:31,943 --> 00:27:35,555
Look at me, I have to sign!

322
00:27:37,191 --> 00:27:39,776
Cover the irons, lazybones!

323
00:27:41,735 --> 00:27:43,142
Damn it!

324
00:27:43,911 --> 00:27:45,983
Zidore!

325
00:28:15,879 --> 00:28:19,621
Not the hospital!
Bring him home!

326
00:28:19,719 --> 00:28:21,542
You're all the same!

327
00:28:21,639 --> 00:28:23,581
We build hospitals
and you won't use them.

328
00:28:23,688 --> 00:28:25,728
The hospital is free.

329
00:28:25,831 --> 00:28:27,620
I have money!

330
00:28:27,720 --> 00:28:30,567
I'd go if I could,
but they don't want me.

331
00:28:30,664 --> 00:28:34,079
Be sensible.
Save your money for when he's out.

332
00:28:36,520 --> 00:28:39,041
It might be a long time
before he's on a roof again.

333
00:28:39,144 --> 00:28:40,770
I have all that's needed!

334
00:28:40,872 --> 00:28:42,279
Step aside.

335
00:28:42,376 --> 00:28:44,743
Rue Polonceau!

336
00:28:45,480 --> 00:28:46,887
The hospital is free.

337
00:28:46,984 --> 00:28:49,351
I want to care for him.
He's my husband.

338
00:28:49,448 --> 00:28:51,172
So, no shop?

339
00:28:51,272 --> 00:28:53,312
No shop.
You can't have everything.

340
00:28:53,416 --> 00:28:56,732
I'll work it out with the landlord.

341
00:29:09,705 --> 00:29:12,803
Six months later, he was healed.

342
00:29:12,905 --> 00:29:16,549
But after paying the doctor's fees,

343
00:29:16,649 --> 00:29:18,471
we had nothing left.

344
00:29:23,145 --> 00:29:26,309
Know what time it is?
Bedtime.

345
00:29:26,408 --> 00:29:28,612
We're up to our ears in work.

346
00:29:28,713 --> 00:29:30,655
I have to go back
right after dinner.

347
00:29:30,761 --> 00:29:32,321
Again?

348
00:29:35,881 --> 00:29:37,769
- How was work?
- I worked the bellows.

349
00:29:37,865 --> 00:29:39,589
He's doing well.

350
00:29:39,690 --> 00:29:41,577
In a bad mood?

351
00:29:41,673 --> 00:29:43,877
I don't have the time.

352
00:29:43,977 --> 00:29:46,530
You should've put me in the hospital.
I'd be healed,

353
00:29:47,210 --> 00:29:49,119
and you'd have your shop.

354
00:29:49,225 --> 00:29:50,632
Oh, be quiet.

355
00:29:56,265 --> 00:29:57,988
You need 500 francs to rent it?

356
00:29:58,089 --> 00:30:00,129
Yes, 500.

357
00:30:00,234 --> 00:30:01,313
Why?

358
00:30:01,418 --> 00:30:03,622
I'll lend them to you.

359
00:30:04,521 --> 00:30:08,864
My mother left me 500 francs.
I'm not doing anything with them.

360
00:30:14,186 --> 00:30:16,641
I won't take your money.

361
00:30:17,770 --> 00:30:19,428
Why not?

362
00:30:20,265 --> 00:30:21,826
There's no reason to.

363
00:30:21,930 --> 00:30:23,337
Yes, there is.

364
00:30:23,434 --> 00:30:25,638
Having a shop would make you happy

365
00:30:26,378 --> 00:30:29,062
and making you happy
makes me happy.

366
00:30:29,162 --> 00:30:31,845
No better reason than that.

367
00:30:46,891 --> 00:30:48,778
SHOP FOR RENT

368
00:30:53,387 --> 00:30:56,104
What are you doing in there?

369
00:30:57,258 --> 00:30:59,200
Nothing.

370
00:30:59,307 --> 00:31:02,471
- And you?
- Me? Nothing.

371
00:31:02,570 --> 00:31:04,131
I came to have a look.

372
00:31:04,234 --> 00:31:05,663
To look at the shop?

373
00:31:07,595 --> 00:31:08,522
Sure.

374
00:31:09,515 --> 00:31:11,075
Me too!

375
00:31:16,939 --> 00:31:17,867
Well?

376
00:31:18,859 --> 00:31:24,326
No, all that money to pay back,
I wouldn't sleep a wink.

377
00:31:25,483 --> 00:31:27,655
I got my shop.

378
00:31:28,811 --> 00:31:31,528
And two weeks ago, what did I see?

379
00:31:31,627 --> 00:31:33,034
Virginie.

380
00:31:33,707 --> 00:31:36,555
I'd forgotten all about her.

381
00:31:42,475 --> 00:31:45,475
- Are they fresh?
- Check the eyes. Fresh from Dieppe.

382
00:31:45,579 --> 00:31:47,489
That's what they say.

383
00:32:18,508 --> 00:32:21,355
My word!
It's Gervaise!

384
00:32:21,868 --> 00:32:23,275
Yes, it is.

385
00:32:23,372 --> 00:32:24,933
An old friend.

386
00:32:25,036 --> 00:32:27,557
How funny!

387
00:32:27,660 --> 00:32:29,221
Hilarious...

388
00:32:29,324 --> 00:32:31,212
My husband, Mr. Fish.

389
00:32:31,308 --> 00:32:33,032
Married? Congratulations.

390
00:32:33,133 --> 00:32:36,613
A policeman, as you see. I was so glad
when he was offered a job here,

391
00:32:36,717 --> 00:32:39,083
all the memories and friends
I'd left behind!

392
00:32:39,180 --> 00:32:41,668
And you, dear?
Working around here?

393
00:32:41,773 --> 00:32:44,228
- I'm a laundress.
- It's not too heavy?

394
00:32:44,332 --> 00:32:46,885
Heavier it is, happier I am.
I'm my own boss.

395
00:32:46,989 --> 00:32:48,199
Really?

396
00:32:48,301 --> 00:32:49,861
Yes.

397
00:32:49,965 --> 00:32:52,867
That's great.
She's her own boss.

398
00:32:52,973 --> 00:32:54,696
Married, too!

399
00:32:54,797 --> 00:32:56,837
My dear, you've come a long way!

400
00:32:56,941 --> 00:32:58,981
Drafty here, isn't it?

401
00:32:59,085 --> 00:33:02,085
- Yes, it certainly is.
- It's from downstairs.

402
00:33:02,189 --> 00:33:04,775
- Won't you come in?
- You live there?

403
00:33:04,877 --> 00:33:07,081
What's funny about that?

404
00:33:07,181 --> 00:33:09,003
I lived there for three years.

405
00:33:09,101 --> 00:33:11,468
How funny...

406
00:33:11,565 --> 00:33:13,125
Hilarious.

407
00:33:13,229 --> 00:33:15,433
Please, come in.

408
00:33:15,534 --> 00:33:18,533
- I have laundry to deliver.
- My neighbor's out shopping.

409
00:33:21,133 --> 00:33:23,500
You know how it is
when you first move in...

410
00:33:31,854 --> 00:33:33,414
It's changed.

411
00:33:35,118 --> 00:33:36,906
The bed used to be this way.

412
00:33:37,006 --> 00:33:39,046
I had my daughter there.

413
00:33:39,149 --> 00:33:42,466
- You have a daughter, too?
- Yes, Nana.

414
00:33:44,366 --> 00:33:46,984
A year after I married Coupeau.

415
00:33:49,582 --> 00:33:51,175
You might remember him,

416
00:33:52,014 --> 00:33:54,982
he's the roofer
who lived in my building.

417
00:33:55,886 --> 00:33:58,253
Sorry to interrupt,
but I'm back on duty at 2:00

418
00:33:58,350 --> 00:34:00,172
and you won't have time
to cook my mackerel.

419
00:34:00,270 --> 00:34:01,993
Sorry, it's my fault.

420
00:34:02,926 --> 00:34:04,966
Clean it, it'll keep you busy.

421
00:34:05,070 --> 00:34:08,845
He likes it. He enjoys popping
the bladder with this foot!

422
00:34:09,903 --> 00:34:12,423
Well, see you soon, Mrs. Fish.

423
00:34:12,527 --> 00:34:14,250
See you soon, Mrs. Coupeau.

424
00:34:14,351 --> 00:34:17,612
I'm glad to see you.
It's been so long.

425
00:34:19,087 --> 00:34:20,909
Shall we talk about it or not?

426
00:34:22,127 --> 00:34:23,534
It's up to you.

427
00:34:23,631 --> 00:34:27,242
Then we'll never mention
the washhouse again.

428
00:34:27,343 --> 00:34:28,139
Okay.

429
00:34:28,239 --> 00:34:30,311
You had a good reason.

430
00:34:30,415 --> 00:34:33,895
You did! She might be my sister,
but she's a nasty bitch.

431
00:34:33,999 --> 00:34:36,999
- Let's not discuss that.
- And you know Lantier.

432
00:34:37,102 --> 00:34:38,663
Listen.

433
00:34:39,823 --> 00:34:41,863
This might make you happy.

434
00:34:43,055 --> 00:34:44,779
They're not together anymore.

435
00:34:45,455 --> 00:34:47,342
- They're not?
- No.

436
00:34:48,015 --> 00:34:50,502
What if he came back to you?

437
00:34:50,607 --> 00:34:52,167
Lantier?

438
00:34:52,271 --> 00:34:55,238
- Why do you say that?
- No reason.

439
00:34:55,343 --> 00:34:57,165
Men are so funny.

440
00:34:57,999 --> 00:34:59,942
He'd be wasting his time.

441
00:35:00,047 --> 00:35:02,152
All that's over.

442
00:35:02,831 --> 00:35:05,133
Dead and buried.

443
00:35:05,232 --> 00:35:06,639
See you soon, Mrs. Coupeau.

444
00:35:09,584 --> 00:35:11,144
Ready?

445
00:35:14,320 --> 00:35:16,142
That was a nice one!

446
00:35:31,792 --> 00:35:33,996
- Hello, Gervaise.
- Hello.

447
00:35:34,992 --> 00:35:36,880
Etienne!

448
00:35:38,832 --> 00:35:40,327
Hello.

449
00:35:40,432 --> 00:35:42,254
- Bye, mother.
- Bye.

450
00:35:43,120 --> 00:35:45,225
- Have a nice day.
- Thanks.

451
00:36:04,272 --> 00:36:05,833
Hello!

452
00:36:07,504 --> 00:36:09,163
Hello.

453
00:36:09,841 --> 00:36:12,077
I'd never have recognized Coupeau.

454
00:36:12,177 --> 00:36:13,453
Who?

455
00:36:13,552 --> 00:36:16,869
That's not him.
That's Goujet, the blacksmith.

456
00:36:20,113 --> 00:36:22,601
He's our best friend.

457
00:36:23,281 --> 00:36:24,623
He took my son as an apprentice.

458
00:36:25,777 --> 00:36:27,184
Blacksmith?

459
00:36:27,281 --> 00:36:30,151
Why not a roofer like his -
like Coupeau?

460
00:36:30,257 --> 00:36:32,145
A roofer?

461
00:36:32,241 --> 00:36:34,762
Coupeau refused
after he hurt his leg.

462
00:36:34,865 --> 00:36:36,589
- Accident?
- Yes.

463
00:36:36,690 --> 00:36:38,250
Let me help you.

464
00:36:38,353 --> 00:36:39,914
No, thanks.

465
00:36:40,753 --> 00:36:42,793
He fell off a roof, poor dear.

466
00:36:42,898 --> 00:36:44,785
He's better now.

467
00:36:46,738 --> 00:36:49,105
You've got a fine shop!

468
00:36:51,634 --> 00:36:53,357
Not bad, is it?

469
00:36:54,033 --> 00:36:55,440
How about a coffee?

470
00:36:55,538 --> 00:36:58,702
I don't want to bother you.

471
00:36:58,802 --> 00:37:01,169
It's no bother. It's ready.

472
00:37:01,265 --> 00:37:04,080
What's the blacksmith's name?
Goujet?

473
00:37:05,809 --> 00:37:07,370
Yes, Goujet.

474
00:37:07,473 --> 00:37:11,980
Between a blacksmith and a roofer,
you chose the roofer!

475
00:37:12,082 --> 00:37:14,537
I didn't choose.

476
00:37:14,641 --> 00:37:18,384
I only met Goujet
the day I married Coupeau.

477
00:37:20,018 --> 00:37:22,473
- Too late.
- I didn't say that.

478
00:37:24,082 --> 00:37:27,116
For me, Coupeau is the best.

479
00:37:27,219 --> 00:37:28,146
Here.

480
00:37:29,074 --> 00:37:30,897
It looks good.

481
00:37:30,994 --> 00:37:33,842
I didn't really want
to get married,

482
00:37:33,939 --> 00:37:35,761
as I had two children already.

483
00:37:35,859 --> 00:37:38,063
This is Nana. Say hello.

484
00:37:38,739 --> 00:37:40,146
Hello.

485
00:37:40,818 --> 00:37:44,462
- All the more reason!
- No. It's like I told him,

486
00:37:44,562 --> 00:37:46,123
it's no gift to give a man.

487
00:37:46,226 --> 00:37:49,226
Why did I tell her all that?

488
00:37:50,099 --> 00:37:53,896
I even told her that Goujet
lent us the money for the shop.

489
00:37:54,643 --> 00:37:57,163
I told her,
"l didn 't really want to,

490
00:37:57,267 --> 00:37:59,820
but Coupeau accepted. "

491
00:38:01,938 --> 00:38:04,142
Coupeau did the right thing!

492
00:38:04,818 --> 00:38:06,728
Yes, he did.

493
00:38:06,834 --> 00:38:11,537
At first, I was afraid,
but each month we've repaid him.

494
00:38:12,659 --> 00:38:16,620
Already 200 francs -

495
00:38:16,723 --> 00:38:20,520
No, 200 francs as of tomorrow.

496
00:38:20,628 --> 00:38:22,831
- Hello, Gervaise.
- Hello.

497
00:38:25,619 --> 00:38:27,986
- I'll be off.
- Stay a while.

498
00:38:28,083 --> 00:38:29,807
I can't, and you're busy.

499
00:38:29,907 --> 00:38:32,755
Besides, with a husband like mine...

500
00:38:33,427 --> 00:38:35,631
He can't survive
without milk in his coffee!

501
00:38:35,732 --> 00:38:37,139
- See you soon.
- Good-bye.

502
00:38:38,292 --> 00:38:40,747
- Sorry!
- Don't worry about it.

503
00:38:42,867 --> 00:38:44,842
Hey!

504
00:38:46,324 --> 00:38:48,909
- Mrs. Boche!
- In person!

505
00:38:49,012 --> 00:38:50,605
What are you doing here?

506
00:38:50,708 --> 00:38:52,268
I take care of the building.

507
00:38:52,371 --> 00:38:54,062
Didn't Gervaise tell you?

508
00:38:54,164 --> 00:38:55,986
How about that?

509
00:38:56,084 --> 00:39:00,143
We helped her get that pretty shop.
- It seems to be doing well.

510
00:39:00,243 --> 00:39:01,650
Depends on the day.

511
00:39:01,748 --> 00:39:02,992
Why?

512
00:39:03,956 --> 00:39:06,345
Got time for a coffee?

513
00:39:06,452 --> 00:39:08,973
Come on.
- Of course.

514
00:39:23,092 --> 00:39:23,953
One...

515
00:39:25,397 --> 00:39:26,607
two...

516
00:39:27,636 --> 00:39:29,043
three...

517
00:39:30,356 --> 00:39:31,883
four.

518
00:39:34,485 --> 00:39:36,176
Mine's rounder.

519
00:39:36,276 --> 00:39:37,837
Mine looks like a heart!

520
00:39:42,517 --> 00:39:45,234
There!
Now we'll be cooler.

521
00:39:47,796 --> 00:39:50,000
I must have caught cold last night.

522
00:39:50,101 --> 00:39:52,949
When you sleep with men,
they're always uncovering you!

523
00:39:53,044 --> 00:39:54,932
Don't talk that way
in front of the child!

524
00:39:55,029 --> 00:39:57,134
Put that on!

525
00:39:58,037 --> 00:40:01,037
Naughty, naughty!
Need help?

526
00:40:04,117 --> 00:40:06,004
Here's Coupeau!

527
00:40:06,101 --> 00:40:08,240
What an entrance!

528
00:40:12,213 --> 00:40:14,580
Don't touch anything!
We're busy.

529
00:40:15,253 --> 00:40:18,253
