01:18:56,802 --> 01:18:59,485
What we want is their hearts

1051
01:18:59,586 --> 01:19:02,269
But they think only of our rears

1052
01:19:02,370 --> 01:19:04,890
They may call us heavenly

1053
01:19:04,994 --> 01:19:07,896
Or name us as goddesses triumphant

1054
01:19:08,002 --> 01:19:12,193
Still they return obstinately

1055
01:19:12,290 --> 01:19:16,830
To our little firmament

1056
01:19:18,338 --> 01:19:19,767
What's so funny?

1057
01:19:19,875 --> 01:19:22,875
"Her little firmament."
Don't you get it?

1058
01:19:25,922 --> 01:19:27,745
Didn't you teach her anything?

1059
01:19:31,362 --> 01:19:33,337
Mes Bottes!

1060
01:19:34,019 --> 01:19:35,742
What did you do with Coupeau?

1061
01:19:35,843 --> 01:19:38,047
Come here!
- I didn't eat him!

1062
01:19:39,715 --> 01:19:42,202
- Where is he?
- Hey! What's your problem?

1063
01:19:46,211 --> 01:19:48,600
He didn't come home last night,
you know.

1064
01:19:49,635 --> 01:19:52,002
I know, neither did l!

1065
01:19:53,475 --> 01:19:55,842
We were together.
- Where's he now?

1066
01:19:57,795 --> 01:20:00,478
He mentioned going to Les Halles
for some snails.

1067
01:20:04,483 --> 01:20:07,483
Thanks, Virginie.
I had a great time.

1068
01:20:07,588 --> 01:20:09,955
- Good night.
- Be good!

1069
01:20:11,683 --> 01:20:13,723
She's so silly, Virginie.

1070
01:20:13,827 --> 01:20:15,802
There you are!

1071
01:20:16,483 --> 01:20:19,647
- About time.
- What is it? Is he hurt?

1072
01:20:20,676 --> 01:20:25,662
In his state,
I should have put him in jail,

1073
01:20:25,764 --> 01:20:27,422
but since we're friends -

1074
01:20:27,524 --> 01:20:29,564
- Did you see?
- Even though he puked on me.

1075
01:20:29,668 --> 01:20:32,516
- Did you see my sidewalk?
- It really stinks.

1076
01:20:48,132 --> 01:20:49,758
He'll be in so much trouble!

1077
01:20:50,596 --> 01:20:52,800
Go to bed.
It's none of our business.

1078
01:21:06,404 --> 01:21:07,811
The slob.

1079
01:21:08,484 --> 01:21:10,524
He didn't.

1080
01:22:55,846 --> 01:22:57,407
Come, my little Gervaise.

1081
01:22:57,511 --> 01:23:00,359
No, I'm staying here.

1082
01:23:01,191 --> 01:23:03,362
What are you afraid of?

1083
01:23:03,463 --> 01:23:05,536
He can't hear us.

1084
01:23:05,639 --> 01:23:07,549
I promise I won't touch you.

1085
01:23:09,831 --> 01:23:11,392
You're hurting me.

1086
01:23:12,583 --> 01:23:13,990
No!

1087
01:23:15,815 --> 01:23:18,335
Oh, God!

1088
01:23:19,175 --> 01:23:21,117
He threw me out of bed.

1089
01:23:22,599 --> 01:23:24,421
I don't even have a bed.

1090
01:24:24,808 --> 01:24:27,175
- Awake already?
- It's time.

1091
01:24:39,049 --> 01:24:41,121
I slept on a chair.

1092
01:24:42,281 --> 01:24:44,964
I'd have given you my bed.

1093
01:24:55,657 --> 01:24:59,519
My poor child, what could I tell him?

1094
01:25:00,681 --> 01:25:01,609
Nothing.

1095
01:25:01,705 --> 01:25:03,528
He no longer loves his mother,
that's all.

1096
01:25:06,121 --> 01:25:10,725
And the only one who loved me,
the only one who could've stopped it,

1097
01:25:10,825 --> 01:25:12,386
had to be in prison.

1098
01:25:15,625 --> 01:25:17,349
And now that he 's back,

1099
01:25:18,345 --> 01:25:20,287
how can I tell him?

1100
01:25:21,289 --> 01:25:23,493
He 'd never understand.

1101
01:25:26,090 --> 01:25:27,813
It seems I 'm too late,

1102
01:25:28,649 --> 01:25:30,853
from what I 've seen.
- What did you see?

1103
01:25:31,689 --> 01:25:33,577
I told you, nothing's going on!

1104
01:25:36,490 --> 01:25:37,438
Don't you believe me?

1105
01:25:39,305 --> 01:25:40,712
I believe you.

1106
01:25:42,570 --> 01:25:44,163
You see?

1107
01:25:45,002 --> 01:25:46,563
Because it's the truth.

1108
01:25:47,306 --> 01:25:48,484
Come on.

1109
01:25:48,586 --> 01:25:49,993
Dance with me.

1110
01:26:08,010 --> 01:26:10,050
I was wrong to go to jail.

1111
01:26:10,154 --> 01:26:11,715
That's for sure!

1112
01:26:13,162 --> 01:26:14,722
But I went,

1113
01:26:15,402 --> 01:26:17,126
and in the meantime,
Lantier moved in.

1114
01:26:17,803 --> 01:26:19,843
It was Coupeau who wanted it!

1115
01:26:20,523 --> 01:26:22,410
Sure it was.

1116
01:26:26,411 --> 01:26:28,233
Why'd you let him?

1117
01:26:28,331 --> 01:26:30,153
I was wrong, I know.

1118
01:26:33,066 --> 01:26:35,816
Gervaise always wants
to please everyone.

1119
01:26:36,491 --> 01:26:38,858
If I had slept with him,

1120
01:26:38,955 --> 01:26:40,711
you know I'd tell you.

1121
01:26:41,227 --> 01:26:42,340
No.

1122
01:26:43,019 --> 01:26:44,425
Why would you?

1123
01:26:45,803 --> 01:26:47,777
I tell you everything.

1124
01:26:47,883 --> 01:26:49,770
You wouldn't tell me.

1125
01:26:49,867 --> 01:26:52,551
You'd be ashamed.
- Good God, yes.

1126
01:26:52,651 --> 01:26:54,277
I would be ashamed.

1127
01:26:56,011 --> 01:26:57,571
Do you believe me?

1128
01:27:01,291 --> 01:27:02,852
I believe you.

1129
01:28:12,045 --> 01:28:13,289
I knew it.

1130
01:28:41,294 --> 01:28:42,854
- Not finished?
- No.

1131
01:28:42,958 --> 01:28:44,518
I'm in no mood to laugh.

1132
01:28:45,517 --> 01:28:47,339
And you, what do you think?

1133
01:28:47,437 --> 01:28:49,641
- Of what?
- Etienne.

1134
01:28:50,349 --> 01:28:51,909
Should we let him go
with Goujet?

1135
01:28:52,013 --> 01:28:54,380
A worker should travel!

1136
01:28:54,478 --> 01:28:56,845
I thought you'd come
to help raise him.

1137
01:28:56,942 --> 01:29:00,422
- He's already been raised.
- I already said no.

1138
01:29:00,526 --> 01:29:03,842
He's just starting out,
it's crazy. I said no.

1139
01:29:03,949 --> 01:29:06,153
- I say yes.
- Who asked you?

1140
01:29:07,470 --> 01:29:09,292
I'm his father.

1141
01:29:11,630 --> 01:29:14,313
That's true.
You're right. Sorry.

1142
01:29:17,230 --> 01:29:20,393
- Got any tobacco?
- Who knows? Look around.

1143
01:29:28,014 --> 01:29:29,421
Why are mornings so rough?

1144
01:29:30,734 --> 01:29:32,141
It's simple:
You drink too much.

1145
01:29:32,238 --> 01:29:34,442
It's not too much,
it does me good!

1146
01:29:34,542 --> 01:29:36,746
- If you say so.
- I'm healthier than you!

1147
01:29:37,998 --> 01:29:40,518
Look at that!
Tight as a drum!

1148
01:29:40,622 --> 01:29:43,688
You should get one.

1149
01:29:43,791 --> 01:29:45,613
Unhealthy fat.

1150
01:29:45,711 --> 01:29:47,653
You're jealous because
you don't have any.

1151
01:29:50,990 --> 01:29:52,998
Typical, no matches.

1152
01:29:53,102 --> 01:29:54,509
Lantier was right.

1153
01:29:54,607 --> 01:29:56,647
Drink was killing Coupeau.

1154
01:29:57,358 --> 01:30:00,141
There were days I thought,
"Good riddance."

1155
01:30:01,455 --> 01:30:03,495
- What are you looking for?
- My suitcase.

1156
01:30:04,815 --> 01:30:07,019
Is Etienne leaving tomorrow?

1157
01:30:07,119 --> 01:30:09,159
You know he is. Go to sleep.

1158
01:30:09,263 --> 01:30:11,086
Daddy took your suitcase.

1159
01:30:13,839 --> 01:30:14,766
Why?

1160
01:30:14,863 --> 01:30:16,685
For the pawnshop.

1161
01:30:20,527 --> 01:30:24,324
He put sheets in it,
your customers' sheets.

1162
01:30:34,031 --> 01:30:35,438
Thief.

1163
01:30:46,511 --> 01:30:47,591
Thief!

1164
01:31:04,784 --> 01:31:06,508
Shut the door!

1165
01:31:19,312 --> 01:31:22,062
The sheets. Tell me!

1166
01:31:22,160 --> 01:31:24,844
Where are my sheets?
- Your sheets.

1167
01:31:24,945 --> 01:31:26,767
Did you pawn them?

1168
01:31:27,856 --> 01:31:29,679
They weren't your sheets!

1169
01:31:30,353 --> 01:31:31,760
Thief!

1170
01:31:31,857 --> 01:31:34,856
That's enough, I said!

1171
01:31:35,536 --> 01:31:38,536
Give me the pawn slip!

1172
01:31:38,641 --> 01:31:40,201
That tickles!

1173
01:31:48,273 --> 01:31:49,931
It's a pawn slip.

1174
01:31:50,609 --> 01:31:52,813
Here's what I think
of your pawn slip!

1175
01:31:55,889 --> 01:31:57,449
I ate your sheets!

1176
01:32:02,450 --> 01:32:03,529
Slob!

1177
01:32:06,513 --> 01:32:08,968
- Leaving so soon?
- I'll be back!

1178
01:32:21,553 --> 01:32:24,073
Gervaise!

1179
01:32:28,273 --> 01:32:30,575
This can't go on.
I'm not leaving.

1180
01:32:30,674 --> 01:32:33,194
You must leave.

1181
01:32:34,289 --> 01:32:36,013
"You must leave."

1182
01:32:36,690 --> 01:32:39,952
He must leave.
Obey your father.

1183
01:32:40,050 --> 01:32:41,610
You must leave.

1184
01:34:09,556 --> 01:34:11,760
They were the only
good things in my life.

1185
01:34:12,436 --> 01:34:14,258
Maybe that's why they left.

1186
01:34:30,356 --> 01:34:33,039
- Virginie's pillowcase.
- So what?

1187
01:34:33,140 --> 01:34:34,547
Smell it.

1188
01:34:35,860 --> 01:34:37,267
Heliotrope.

1189
01:34:37,940 --> 01:34:39,762
Remind you of anything?

1190
01:35:18,997 --> 01:35:20,721
What's your problem?

1191
01:35:38,998 --> 01:35:41,616
Gervaise, this is the last straw!

1192
01:35:41,717 --> 01:35:43,441
You call this clean?

1193
01:35:43,542 --> 01:35:45,102
It's still greasy.

1194
01:35:47,957 --> 01:35:50,739
Maybe if Mr. Boche didn't put
that dirty pomade in his hair!

1195
01:35:50,837 --> 01:35:52,244
Mr. Boche?

1196
01:35:52,342 --> 01:35:54,065
He does his hair as he likes!

1197
01:35:55,158 --> 01:35:57,427
Fine, I'll do it again.

1198
01:35:58,102 --> 01:36:00,142
And you, my dear,
are losing your touch!

1199
01:36:00,245 --> 01:36:01,969
I'm not losing my touch,
I'm working alone

1200
01:36:02,070 --> 01:36:03,793
and I've only got
one set of hands!

1201
01:36:04,629 --> 01:36:07,793
One last thing,
the owner comes tomorrow.

1202
01:36:07,894 --> 01:36:09,301
I know.

1203
01:36:09,398 --> 01:36:12,464
I'm only 10 days late.
- Only 10?

1204
01:36:13,142 --> 01:36:15,029
First, it's 13.

1205
01:36:15,126 --> 01:36:18,126
And second,
he's thrown people out for less!

1206
01:36:19,830 --> 01:36:22,034
More respectable people!

1207
01:36:33,527 --> 01:36:35,567
That's one less client.

1208
01:36:36,534 --> 01:36:38,574
One less source of disgust.

1209
01:36:40,183 --> 01:36:41,743
And 10 francs less every month.

1210
01:36:41,847 --> 01:36:43,635
Don't bug me!

1211
01:36:43,735 --> 01:36:45,491
Mind your own business!

1212
01:36:45,591 --> 01:36:48,274
It is my business when
you owe me two weeks pay!

1213
01:36:48,375 --> 01:36:50,197
I never said I didn't.

1214
01:36:52,951 --> 01:36:54,358
They don't deprive themselves.

1215
01:36:56,599 --> 01:36:58,421
Where's my glass?

1216
01:36:58,519 --> 01:37:00,275
Come and get it, lazybones.

1217
01:37:00,375 --> 01:37:02,197
Is that how you
speak to your father?

1218
01:37:03,383 --> 01:37:04,944
It wasn't me.

1219
01:37:07,479 --> 01:37:09,072
Stew, again!

1220
01:37:09,751 --> 01:37:11,791
Drat! I've had it!

1221
01:37:15,959 --> 01:37:16,887
Slob!

1222
01:37:19,639 --> 01:37:23,120
Who did that?
- We're sick of potatoes.

1223
01:37:23,223 --> 01:37:25,492
Give me money
and we'll have meat.

1224
01:37:26,359 --> 01:37:28,302
Give me that!
- Bye! I'm going to eat.

1225
01:37:28,407 --> 01:37:30,546
You're lucky, I'm sick of potatoes!

1226
01:37:30,647 --> 01:37:33,964
It might not be your fault,
but lately, you must admit -

1227
01:37:34,968 --> 01:37:37,488
And you,
do you pay my alimony?

1228
01:37:37,592 --> 01:37:38,672
Come on.

1229
01:37:38,775 --> 01:37:42,256
"Come on," what's that mean?
Come on, come on.

1230
01:37:43,256 --> 01:37:45,078
You'll drive me crazy.

1231
01:37:49,848 --> 01:37:51,888
I don't like potatoes either!

1232
01:37:57,240 --> 01:37:59,062
If that's how you feel, I'll leave.

1233
01:38:01,016 --> 01:38:03,886
Great! Go away.

1234
01:38:04,888 --> 01:38:06,448
And don't come back.

1235
01:38:09,400 --> 01:38:11,604
- We can't go on like this.
- No.

1236
01:38:11,704 --> 01:38:13,613
To say such things...

1237
01:38:14,456 --> 01:38:16,496
When the trough is empty,
we fight like beasts.

1238
01:38:20,056 --> 01:38:22,096
What if I found someone
to take over the shop?

1239
01:38:22,201 --> 01:38:25,517
Right away!
I'll close up shop and good riddance!

1240
01:38:25,625 --> 01:38:27,031
Are you crazy?

1241
01:38:28,921 --> 01:38:30,895
We'll find someone.

1242
01:38:31,576 --> 01:38:32,983
I don't know.

1243
01:38:33,817 --> 01:38:35,377
Think about it.

1244
01:38:38,297 --> 01:38:40,119
I can't believe it.

1245
01:38:40,217 --> 01:38:41,940
Why did you say that?

1246
01:38:42,041 --> 01:38:43,863
Your shop, don't you remember?

1247
01:38:44,985 --> 01:38:46,392
Your shop.

1248
01:38:47,065 --> 01:38:48,887
Yes, I wanted my shop.

1249
01:38:50,201 --> 01:38:52,089
Lord, how I wanted it!

1250
01:38:52,601 --> 01:38:54,161
And I got it.

1251
01:38:54,265 --> 01:38:57,811
And now, where's my shop?

1252
01:38:59,450 --> 01:39:01,272
You two ate it.

1253
01:39:01,370 --> 01:39:03,410
It's in your belly and his.

1254
01:39:04,729 --> 01:39:07,413
My God, we were
better off as employees.

1255
01:39:08,473 --> 01:39:12,751
I don't want it anymore.
I can't stand it. They can have it.

1256
01:39:29,338 --> 01:39:32,338
Get your crocks and china
fixed here!

1257
01:39:37,562 --> 01:39:39,122
May I join you?

1258
01:39:40,025 --> 01:39:41,848
Not having lunch at home?

1259
01:39:42,362 --> 01:39:44,336
Give him a bag, too.

1260
01:39:44,442 --> 01:39:46,646
You're right, it's gone too far.

1261
01:39:47,642 --> 01:39:49,465
You won't see me around there
much longer!

1262
01:39:50,458 --> 01:39:52,018
What a pity.

1263
01:39:52,122 --> 01:39:54,010
As if you care.

1264
01:39:54,106 --> 01:39:56,048
That's not a nice thing to say!

1265
01:40:07,003 --> 01:40:09,686
Isn't it beautiful?
Care to join me?

1266
01:40:09,786 --> 01:40:13,015
- Are you alone?
- If I were, I wouldn't invite you.

1267
01:40:13,115 --> 01:40:14,937
In that case, thanks.

1268
01:40:15,035 --> 01:40:16,442
Good-bye, Clemence.

1269
01:40:16,539 --> 01:40:17,946
I'll bring my fries.

1270
01:40:18,043 --> 01:40:19,603
If you want.

1271
01:40:20,923 --> 01:40:22,832
My regards to Mr. Fish!

1272
01:40:27,643 --> 01:40:29,683
Actually, no.

1273
01:40:31,803 --> 01:40:34,105
I have no desire
to give up my shop.

1274
01:40:34,203 --> 01:40:35,610
Sorry!

1275
01:40:35,963 --> 01:40:38,963
Make up your mind.
Didn't you say you did?

1276
01:40:39,067 --> 01:40:40,627
Give up my shop?

1277
01:40:40,731 --> 01:40:42,968
On the contrary!

1278
01:40:43,803 --> 01:40:45,526
I'll hire new workers,

1279
01:40:45,627 --> 01:40:47,831
I'll pay my debts,
I'll begin afresh!

1280
01:40:47,932 --> 01:40:50,136
You'll see,
don't you worry!

1281
01:40:50,812 --> 01:40:53,594
I wanted to help you,
out of friendship.

1282
01:40:53,692 --> 01:40:55,099
Oh, yes!

1283
01:40:55,771 --> 01:40:57,397
Out of friendship.

1284
01:40:58,267 --> 01:41:00,122
Friendship is a fine thing,

1285
01:41:01,499 --> 01:41:03,442
and fine friends you are!

1286
01:41:03,547 --> 01:41:07,289
- Or you simply changed your mind?
- I changed my mind

1287
01:41:07,387 --> 01:41:10,038
as soon as I saw her nasty puss
behind you!

1288
01:41:10,140 --> 01:41:12,441
You haven't changed!

1289
01:41:13,468 --> 01:41:16,948
You're still the same trash
I spanked at the wash house.

1290
01:41:17,052 --> 01:41:18,939
- Come on.
- You shouldn't have said that.

1291
01:41:19,036 --> 01:41:20,858
I get it now.

1292
01:41:21,532 --> 01:41:23,987
Ever since then,
this is what you wanted,

1293
01:41:24,092 --> 01:41:26,459
with those big innocent eyes!

1294
01:41:26,556 --> 01:41:28,411
You won't get my shop!

1295
01:41:29,404 --> 01:41:30,965
Don't be so proud.

1296
01:41:31,068 --> 01:41:33,207
We know how you bought it,

1297
01:41:33,308 --> 01:41:35,348
with money from a jailbird.

1298
01:41:35,452 --> 01:41:38,136
He's worth more than your cop,

1299
01:41:38,236 --> 01:41:39,643
slut!
- Slut?

1300
01:41:39,740 --> 01:41:42,904
And you? How can you talk,
with what goes on here?

1301
01:41:43,740 --> 01:41:45,147
Everyone knows.

1302
01:41:46,781 --> 01:41:50,577
- What about you two?
- You're nuts!

1303
01:41:50,685 --> 01:41:54,165
Except everyone
doesn't know about you!

1304
01:41:55,388 --> 01:42:00,058
- Madam, let's go.
- Don't call her "Madam" for my sake!

1305
01:42:00,893 --> 01:42:03,446
Heliotrope seller!

1306
01:42:03,549 --> 01:42:04,956
Get out of my sight!

1307
01:42:05,053 --> 01:42:07,387
- I'm not scared of you.
- You should be!

1308
01:42:08,541 --> 01:42:10,101
You'll end up in prison too!

